.SH "NAME"
pod2test \- Convert embedded tests and code examples to .t files
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  pod2test [\-Mmodule] [input [output]]
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBpod2test\fR is a front-end for Pod::Tests (formerly Test::Inline 1).
It generates TAP-compatible .t testing scripts from embedded tests and
code examples.
.PP
If output is not specified, the resulting .t file will go to \s-1STDOUT\s0.
Otherwise, it will go to the given output file.  If input is not
given, it will draw from \s-1STDIN\s0.
.PP
If the given file contains no tests or code examples, no output will
be given, no output file will be created and pod2test will exit with
1.
.PP
The Test::More module is made available to the testing blocks using
the 'no_plan' feature.  Any further modules which should be used are
specified with \-M. \fB\s-1UNIMPLEMENTED\s0\fR
.SH "BUGS and CAVEATS"
.IX Header "BUGS and CAVEATS"
This is a very simple rough cut.  It only does very rudimentary tests
on the examples.
.SH "SUPPORT"
.IX Header "SUPPORT"
This script has been superceded by \f(CW\*(C`inline2test\*(C'\fR from the newer
Test::Inline 2. Most testing code that currently works with
\&\f(CW\*(C`pod2test\*(C'\fR should continue to work with the new version.
.PP
The most notable exceptions are \f(CW\*(C`=for begin\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`=for end\*(C'\fR, which
are deprecated in the newer version.
.PP
After upgrading Test::Inline, Pod::Tests and \f(CW\*(C`pod2test\*(C'\fR were split
out to provide a compatibility package for legacy code.
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`pod2test\*(C'\fR will stay in \s-1CPAN\s0, but should remain unchanged indefinately,
with the exception of any minor bugs that will require squishing.
.PP
Bugs in this dist should be reported via the following \s-1URL\s0. Feature requests
should not be submitted, as further development is now occuring in
Test::Inline.
.PP
